main event: A series of UFO sightings and photographs related to a Javelin vehicle launch from Wallops Island, Virginia on September 24, 1966.
interesting points: The report includes 5 photographs from different sightings,One photograph shows a bright, glowing object described as a Martian cloud released by a Javelin vehicle,Another sighting involved an object traversing from southwest to northeast,The object in the second sighting was estimated to be 150 to 300 feet long and left a trail of reddish-orange sparks,One of the photographs documents a test of the Javelin vehicle conducted prior to the main event.
sighted object: glowing object, comet-like object, bright beam of light, elongated streak, bright object
witness description: Witness interviewed by Lt. Loucks of the U.S. Air Force.
